<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1025,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1025,1052]" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Metope with distinct median carinae and weak sublateral carinae or without them. Upper margin of metope straight or concave. Coryphe transverse, with anterior margin concave or nearly straight (in dorsal view). Ocelli present. Fore wing with 
<emphasis box="[498,524,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">Sc</emphasis>
distinct, basal cell large, elongately oval, 
<emphasis box="[992,1009,1099,1124]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">R</emphasis>
2–12 (2–4 main branches), firstly furcating closely to basal cell and second branch furcating after wing middle, 
<emphasis box="[995,1018,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">M</emphasis>
2–13 (2–4 main branches), furcating before wing middle, 
<emphasis box="[387,437,1171,1197]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="159">CuA</emphasis>
2–5 (2 main braches), furcating near to wing middle. Hind tibia with 2–4 lateral spines. Phallobase with a high flattened laterally projection below its ventral lobe. Ventral phallobase lobe long and wide, with two long and narrow latero-apical processes. Aedeagus with pair of ventral hooks, often short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
